claim.claim-text:
An directionally filtered indicator light (10) system, comprising

a light source (20) having a display surface (22);

a control system (40), the control system (40) providing power to the light source when a condition or set of conditions are met;

a directional filter (30) arranged adjacent to the display surface (22), the light source (20) transmitting light through the directional filter (30);

wherein the directional filter (30) regulates the transmitted light to within a viewing angle in at least one orthogonal plane; the viewing angle having been selected to permit a first location to receive the transmitted light and to prevent a second location from receiving the transmitted light.

A method for limiting the apparent intensity of an indicator light (10), comprising

providing an indicator light (10) having a display surface (22) with a predetermined size and shape;

preparing a directional filter (30) with approximately the size and the shape of the display surface (22);

determining the orientation of the directional filter (30); and

arranging the directional filter (30) adjacent to the display surface (22), wherein the orientation of the directional filter (30) allows the indicator light (10) to transmit light to a first group of individuals and substantially prevents the indicator light (10) from transmitting light to a second group of individuals.
